Claims WHAT IS CLAIMED IS: 1. A system for natural language processing, the system comprising: a sentence selector comprising a first neural network, for: receiving, at a first encoder of the first neural network, a question and a plurality of sentences that represent a document; determining, using the first encoder and a first decoder of the first neural network, a plurality of scores, wherein a score in the plurality of scores represents whether the question is answerable using a corresponding sentence in the plurality of sentences; generating, using a sentence selector module of the first neural network a minimum set of sentences from the plurality of sentences and the plurality of scores; and a question answering module comprising a second neural network, the question answering module for generating an answer from the minimum set of sentences and the question. 2. The system of claim 1, wherein the first encoder of the first neural network is for: determining sentence embeddings from the plurality of sentences; determining question embeddings from the question; determining question-aware embeddings from the sentence embeddings and the question embeddings; generating, using a first bi-directional long short-term memory (âBiLSTMâ), sentence encodings from the sentence embeddings and the question-aware embeddings; generating, using a second BiLSTM, question encodings from the question embeddings and the question-aware embeddings; and the first decoder in the first neural network for determining the plurality of scores using the sentence encodings and the question encodings. 3. The system of claim 2, wherein the second neural network includes a second encoder for: receiving the minimum set of sentences and the question; generating second sentence encodings and second question encodings from the minimum set of sentences and the question; and 

 the second neural network includes a second decoder for determining, using the second sentence encodings and the second question encodings, an answer range for the answer to the question. 4. The system of claim 3, wherein the second encoder of the second neural network is for: determining second sentence embeddings from sentences in the minimum set of sentences; determining second question embeddings from the question; determining second question-aware embeddings from the second sentence embeddings and the second question embeddings; generating the second sentence encodings from the second sentence embeddings and the second question-aware embeddings; and generating the second question encodings from the second question embeddings and the second question-aware embeddings. 5. The system of claims 3 or 4, wherein the first encoder of the first neural network and the second encoder in the second neural network are a same encoder. 6. The system of any one of claims 1 to 5, wherein a size of the minimum set of sentences varies between the question and another question. 7. The system of any one of claims 1 to 6, wherein a size of the minimum set of sentences includes at least one sentence in the plurality of sentences with a score from the plurality of scores above a threshold. 8. A method for natural language processing, the method comprising: receiving a question and a plurality of sentences that represent a document at a sentence selector that includes a first neural network; 

 determining, using an encoder and a decoder of the first neural network, a plurality of scores, wherein a score in the plurality of scores represents whether the question is answerable using a sentence in the plurality of sentences; generating, by a sentence selector module of the first neural network, a minimum set of sentences from the plurality of sentences and the plurality of scores; and generating, using a question answering module that includes a second neural network, an answer from the minimum set of sentences and the question. 9. The method of claims 8, wherein the encoder of the first neural network is for: determining sentence embeddings from the plurality of sentences; determining question embeddings from the question; determining question-aware embeddings from the sentence embeddings and question embeddings; generating, using a first bi-directional long-short memory (âBiLSTMâ) of the encoder, sentence encodings from the sentence embeddings and the question-aware embeddings; generating, using a second BiLSTM of the encoder, question encodings from the question embeddings and the question-aware embeddings; and wherein the decoder of the first neural network is for determining the plurality of scores using the sentence encodings and the question encodings. 10. The method of claims 8 or 9, further comprising: receiving, at the second neural network, the minimum set of sentences and the question; generating, using the encoder that the second neural network shares with the first neural network, second sentence encodings and second question encodings from the minimum set of sentences and the question; and determining, using the second sentence encodings and the second question encodings, an answer range for the answer to the question. 11. The method of claims 10, further comprising: determining, using the encoder, second sentence embeddings from sentences in the minimum set of sentences; 

 determining, using the encoder, second question embeddings from the question; determining, using the encoder, second question-aware embeddings from the second sentence embeddings and the second question embeddings; generating, using the encoder, the second sentence encodings from the second sentence embeddings and the second question-aware embeddings; and generating, using the encoder, the second question encodings from the second question embeddings and the second question-aware embeddings. 12. The method of any one of claims 8 to 11, wherein a size of the minimum set of sentences varies between the question and another question. 13. The method of any one of claims 8 to 12, wherein a size of the minimum set of sentences includes at least one sentence in the plurality of sentences with a score from the plurality of scores above a threshold. 14. A non-transitory machine-readable medium having stored thereon machine- readable instructions executable to cause a machine to perform operations that process a natural language, the operations comprising: receiving, at an encoder of a first neural network included in a sentence selector, a question and a plurality of sentences that represent a document; determining, by the encoder and a decoder of the first neural network, a plurality of scores, wherein a score in the plurality of scores represents whether the question is answerable using a sentence in the plurality of sentences; generating, by a sentence selection module of the first neural network, a minimum set of sentences from the plurality of scores and the plurality of sentences; and generating, using a question answering module that comprises a second neural network, an answer to the question from the minimum set of sentences and the question. 15. The non-transitory machine-readable medium of claim 14, wherein to determine the plurality of scores, the machine is further configured to perform the operations comprising: determining, using the encoder, sentence embeddings from the plurality of sentences; 

 determining, using the encoder, question embeddings from the question; determining, using the encoder, question-answer embeddings from the sentence embeddings and question embeddings; generating, using a first bi-directional long short-term memory (âBiLSTMâ), sentence encodings from the sentence embeddings and question-aware embeddings; generating, using a second BiLSTM, question encodings from the question embeddings and question-aware embeddings; and determining the plurality of scores using the sentence encodings and the question encodings. 16. The non-transitory machine-readable medium of claim 15, wherein the machine is further configured to perform the operations comprising: receiving, at the encoder of the second neural network that is shared with the first neural network, the minimum set of sentences and the question; generating, using the encoder, second sentence encodings and second question encodings from the minimum set of sentences and the question; and generating, using the second sentence encodings and the second question encodings, an answer range for the answer of the question. 17. The non-transitory machine-readable medium of claim 16, wherein the machine is further configured to perform the operations comprising: determining, using the encoder, second sentence embeddings from sentences in the minimum set of sentences; determining, using the encoder, second question embeddings from the question; determining, using the encoder, second question-aware embeddings from the second sentence embeddings and the second question embeddings; generating the second sentence encodings from the second sentence embeddings and the second question-aware embeddings; and generating the second question encodings from the second question embeddings and the second question-aware embeddings. 18. The non-transitory machine-readable medium of any one of claims 14 to 17, wherein a size of the minimum set of sentences varies between the question and another question. 19. The non-transitory machine-readable medium of any one of claims 14 to 18, wherein a size of the minimum set of sentences includes at least one sentence in the plurality of sentences with a score from the plurality of scores above a threshold. 20. The non-transitory machine-readable medium of any one of claims 14 to 19, wherein the plurality of sentences are sentences from a portion of the document.
